Acting President David Mabuza has on behalf of government and South Africa conveyed condolences to Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi on the sad passing of his mother Mme Sina Seleku Motsoaledi. The Home Affairs Department said Mama Sekeku Sina Motsoaledi passed away peacefully in Pretoria on Thursday morning. “We have learned with sadness of the passing of Minister Motsoaledi’s mother. We thank Mme Motsoaledi for having been a pillar of strength and support for the family during the most challenging time of the struggle for the liberation of South Africa. “We wish to convey our deepest condolences to his family, friends and relatives. May her soul rest in eternal peace,” said Acting President Mabuza. Home Affairs said details of the funeral will be announced in due course. – SAnews.gov.za